entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: hi i am ellie thanks for coming in today i was created to talk to people in a safe and secure environment i am not a therapist but i am here to learn about people and would love to learn about you i will ask a few questions to get us started

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: okay

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: and please feel free to tell me anything your answers are totally confidential are you okay with this

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yes

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay so how are you doing today

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: pretty good a little tired

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is good where are you from originally

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: seattle washington

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: really why would you move to la

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: when i was eighteen my mom and dad decided we wanted to move to california and so we moved down to pasadena actually monrovia first and i have been here ever since

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: yeah do you travel a lot

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no unfortuantely i do not

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: i am sorry

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: that is okay

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how close are you to your family

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i am not my mom and dad are die are dead i have no brothers or sisters and the rest of my family have either moved away or i do not talk to them anymore or like that

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that sounds really hard

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: well i have kind of an attitude that if i have me and friends i have then i am okay

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay what do you do to relax

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: read watch sports when they are available let is see i used to play golf i may do that again some day but not right now because of the cost and the time

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay what are some things that make you really mad

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: people that are rude

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: h what do you do when you are annoyed

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: well usually i ignore it this morning actually i told a guy to stop what he was doing and we got kind of an argent about it and then the argent was over and it was done

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how are you at controlling your temper

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: very good because i had a very bad temper when i was a kid and i told myself i had to control it

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: when was the last time you argued with someone and what was it about

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: this morning about the guy making lots and lots of noise on purpose and in a place that was just not the place to do it i mean it was a public place but and that was it just a little argent and i am done with the argent once i say what i say

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: h what did you do after the military

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i came down here played pool for a nber of years finally graduated from high school which i had dropped out of when i moved went on to college got my bachelor is degree and an aa degree at pasadena and cal state la and started working various jobs and that is about it took care of my mom

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what would you study at school

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: business that was my major i also studied cyclic anthropology and philosphy and history et cetera

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: awesome have you ever been diagnosed with ptsd

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you been diagnosed with depression

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no never depressed

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how easy is it for you to get a good night is sleep

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: lately not so good between the fact that i sleep in my car and it is very cold and then sometimes i do get and with all the things going on in my life right now i i think of things and so and plus i get up at four thirty in the morning

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: yeah i am sorry to hear that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: that is okay

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what are you like when you do not sleep well

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: tired and i get a little grpy sometimes but not very much

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: i understand how have you been feeling lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: tired with all the things i have had to do and weather and sleep

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you noticed any changes in your behavior or thoughts lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: do you feel down

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: a little bit sometimes about how maybe i should have started doing all this years ago
